ECB’s Smaghi Told Italy Won’t Leave, Frankfurter Allgemeine Says

-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 
2011-06-18T08:21:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-18/ecb-s-smaghi-told-italy-won-t-leave-frankfurter-allgemeine-says.html
Lorenzo Bini Smaghi has told the
Italian government that he won’t resign from his position as
executive board member of the  European Central Bank , the
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported, without saying where it
obtained the information.  The ECB, responding to questions about Smaghi ’s future,
yesterday said that board members are appointed for eight years
and take decisions in “full independence.”  To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt at   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  